Amazon Basics Wood Lift-Top Kids Study Desk, White

Multipurpose Kids Desk

Sized for kids ages three to eight, this desk provides ample surface space for coloring, working on puzzles, finishing homework, and more.

Lift-top Drawer for Storage

The desk's safety-hinged lid lifts up to reveal handy storage space for papers, pens, books, and other supplies.

Sturdy Design

The durable desk features reinforced legs for long lasting reliable strength.

Easy Assembly

The desk assembles quickly and easily. All necessary hardware and instructions are included.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      VINE VOICE
      5.0 out of 5 stars Great for kids 2-7!
      Reviewed in the United States on June 6, 2023
      Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
      This was quite easy to assemble. It took me maybe 20 minutes.

      My child is 2 and he usually stands at it to play, or pulls up a step stool or something similar to sit on. I do wish it came with a matching chair - there isn't even one available.

      In general, I don't worry about him making a mess with crayons or anything using this desk, because it is easily wiped up with a cloth or magic eraser. Anything sticky can be wiped up, and it's better to have little dents on this desk than on any of our adult furniture that we'd like to keep past his school years. It does hold up pretty well, though.

      The lift top desk feels stable and secure. The safety hinge is nearly identical to the one I installed on my old cedar trunk when we turned it into his toy box. We store paper, coloring pages, and crayons and there and I am not concerned at all that it will drop on his fingers and hurt him at any point.

      Unless he goes totally werewolf with scissors or toys before he outgrows this desk, I can easily see finding a spot to reuse it, like as a night stand, or being able to donate it to a school/preschool or friend/family in need of child-friendly furniture.

      VINE VOICE
      5.0 out of 5 stars Little bit shorter than anticipated but practical and easy to assemble
      Reviewed in the United States on February 16, 2023
      Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
      My daughter helped me assemble this and it was nice that it all came together in one box with the main top piece and then the legs and bolts to attach (along with an allen key wrench).

      The paint on it was easily scratched, I couldn't tell if it was me when I was putting it together or if it came that way initially. And it was a bit shorter than I figured, so make sure to take a look at measurements but will have to find a lower chair or lower sitting stool for child to work on this.

      The lift-top is nice in that it will stay up once lifted, it has a mechanism that will keep the top propped up so it doesn't have to be held up. This is really nice, particularly with the kids getting stuff in and out of it and is a very nice feature for such an affordable desk.
